content: Such a sweet concept. I love it! It's very relaxing.
Cute interface and character options, but ruined by lack of randomized cards, same opening hand over and over. Fix the randomness and I'll increase the rating to 4-5 stars.

I love this game. I have been playing for a couple of days now, so I havent noticed any of the issues that some people find annoying, but this game is full of character and makes me smile, which is a good thing.
Cozy game

This is app is a delight. It fits so much character into a simple interface. I've seen complaints that raising the difficulty level comprises merely of giving the grandpa better cards. I've played this dozens of times and have not found that to be the case. Luck of the draw, truly, favors or plagues either of you. [Update 2020/11/07] Game still works, except: occasional hand repeats, create grandpa randomizer makes the same second result everytime and won't work after that. Reinstall no help.
Cute. Love that it let's me count my hand myself.

I get the same opening hand over and over... 3,5,6,6,Q,K and a 6 is flipped. I try exiting the game and clearing the cache, but it doesn't always help. This happens on both my Asus phone and Samsung tablet, each running a different version of Android. Oh well, at least it was free.
great game
amazing
Good interface but same cards at start regularly. Also crashes if swap apps. But fun.
Rigged deals. Predetermined outcomes.
Game breaks a lot. Having never played Cribbage it was fun for a while.... Then you notice what others have... The game cheats, cards aren't random, grandpa's "skill" is just the hands he's dealt.

Every time I switch to a different app the game crashes and I can't continue where I left off. Example when I get a text and I check my text and go back to the game it force quits the app and all progress is lost wether its game progress or right at the beginning when making a grandpa. Please fix. Otherwise the game would be excellent.
Really well done cribbage game except it gives you the same hands ever time you start. Dev needs to fix the randomization code because it's unplayable as is.
Dropped this down to one star. The cards are not randomly dealt, as is proved by getting the exact same run of opening cards several times. This leads to a somewhat boring start.
I play this every night before bed to unwind. It's absolutely delightful!

Great interface. Could be improved with more dialogue, music great. Stats could be nice and an ability to review performance. But I think that may take away what is relaxing about the game. Like it alot.

Utterly charming interface that makes learning and playing cribbage a really relaxing and fun experience. I had no idea how to play before this, despite being really into games and trying to learn in other ways. But now I'm even teaching my mum how to play! One or two bugs, with sound continuing outside app, but they do nothing to spoil this experience. Absolutely perfect example of how to make a digital card game engaging! Thanks grandpas
Wholesome and well tuned.
Super cute
It's good game but you can't play other people but before I had this app the game was confusing for me as my uncle tried to teach me but going through it with this app makes it easy to learn
Samsung S20+ works great. Good for passing the time away.
Fun game. Nice customization. Never got my grandfather to play so this is cool.

The game is okay... when it does work. It crashes on a regular basis or doesn't start again after being minimized. Partially bad programming though: choosing a harder difficulty level just translates to "Grandpa's getting better cards." It does work offline though, which I think is very nice. Overall: If you don't mind the small crashing flaws, and if you like playing cribbage on a medium-just-for-fun-level - go get it.
The best game ever
Cute!!

Absolutely Delightful for all non serious cribbage player. And probably serious ones as well. Love the chat from grandpa. And his scoring phrases. Reminds me me of my Dad and that makes me smile as i miss him. For that mr Developer 10 stars. IF YOU PLAY CRIBBAGE YOU WILL LOVE THIS. I did have another cribbage game but that is now deleted. Thankyou Thankyou

Good idea, but difficulty level determines quality of cards dealt, not actual skill or ability of the grandpa. I lost 3 games in a row, almost being skunked each game, on average difficulty because grandpa would get dealt 10-14 point hands every round while I'd get 32 point hands and cribs.
Bahut hard bahut acxha
Difficulty needs to be tweaked. Opponent wins 9 out of 10 matches unless on easiest setting. Feels fixed and unbalanced.
So cute! I love being able to customize the grandpa. The reason I didn't give 5 stars is because I can't name him. I tried typing and nothing worked.
It's really good... but I still don't really know how to play..
Not random at all. Grandpa gets phenomenal hands too consistently. Never seen so many 16 hands in my life
Fun Game. It seems absurd but i think it would be cool to have the option to face your Grandpa's up against each other in a cpu vs. cpu.
great app. friendly atmosphere

It's a garbage game. Their idea of "harder" means the computer gets better cards. Seriously. Doesn't matter the difficulty. Maxed out, AI gets bare minimum 12 pt hands. Every single time. There is no skill involved. This is prefabbed bullshlt. I'm a damn good cribbage player. No amount of "skill" can beat "predetermined cards". I absolutely do not recommend this game to anyone. There are other cribbage games out there. Fairer ones. Please, go play one of them.
Fun and simple. Never played crib before and this helped me learn very easily
One of the best tutorials I've ever played. Great game!
I really love this cribbage app. It's lots of fun to play the card game and it's fun designing the grandpas. I wish they pointed out that the board and scoring appeared as the frame of the app.
Really enjoying this game! Learning the more I play and it's been a lot of fun!
Cute game with nice graphics. Helps me pass my time with ease.✌️
Doesn't work because my OS is too new
This is amazing and very sweet. Thanks for the memories!
The game is great; my only issue is when I'm trying to enter a name I can't type any letters. I can put numbers, but letters won't work.
Cribbage with a twist. The grandpa says things in the game, its funny. No IAP or unnecessary permissions. Definitely recommend.

This app was last updated 3 years ago. The dev has the audacity and cheek to "go free for Corona" but alas due to Android, this being old means android treats it as a virus or unsafe software. Do NOT download and don't bother this until the developer bothers.

Cribbage with Grandpas has been really fun! I finally scored more than my Grandpa a few days ago, and it's been really nice to be taught how to play as opposed to having it auto add up. A worthwhile purchase!

Hey there should be some sort of cloud save for your grandpas. I customized two grandpas to look like my real life deceased grandpas and when I got a new device I lost them all over again. Serious bummer. I know it's a dumb thing to be sad about and after not playing for about a year I finally made two new grandpas but still. That was a bit rough. Just a suggestion.
Doesn't Run. Literally won't open on my Pixelbook. Refunded immediately
Gotta love these grandpas.

userName: Ꮶ ɨ ք ʟ ɨ ռ ɢ
content: In my experience, the AI is the best out of the 4-5 cribbage apps I've tried. Customizing GPas is just icing on the cake. My only quibble is the sad lack of GMas in the game, as it was my GMa Dorothy who taught me the ways of this game of ours when I was a child.
Reasonable phone cribbage game. After a while the game logic is fairly predictable and becomes less interesting.
The absolute best and most charming card game on my phone. It's outlasted nearly every other game I've tried. A perfect thing!
fantastic intro to a classic card game. grandpa creator made me a bit emotional and I missed my own. wish I had gotten a chance to play cards with him.

Most of this game is great; quick gameplay, good AI, fun graphics. A few bugs that I've run across, but usually it just crashes and I can start it up where I left off. The big bug I'm running into, though, is with opening hands; every time I'm first dealer, I'm dealt the exact same opening hand (Q of spades, 5 of hearts, 6 of diamonds, 3 6 and K of spades) and the starter card is the 6 of hearts. It's not a deal breaker, but it's kind of annoying. Without that bug, it's a solid 4-4.5 stars.

Game is smooth and charming, but something is wrong with the randomness; multuple times I've gotten the exact same hand at the start of a game, which isn't very fun. Also, the game doesn't let you switch back to it after switching apps, anf has occasional crashes.
its a great crib game, plus the gandpas are funny!
Best cribbage app hands down! I only miss being able to play short games to 61 points.

I used to play cdibbage with my grandpa all the time, but I'm not able to play with him anymore since he got dimentia. So the fact that I can recreate a grandpa simular to him and play cribbage again is great. This game is alof of fun and very aestheticly pleasing.

Absolutely wonderful. Aside from being clean and functional with no hangs etc it's absolutely gorgeous visually. The art, writing and music comes together to form a comfortably nostalgic atmosphere. For the price of a biscuit with your coffee it's yours and will keep you entertained through many coffee breaks. One minor gripe, with muggings it seems the computer opponents never make a scoring mistake however it may just be unlikely enough that I haven't seen it.
Just like my dad

It is fillled with charm and style. Most Cribbage apps focus solely in the game itself but this app touches on what makes cribbage meaningful: playing with the same people for years on years. Cribbage is about the person sitting across from you. This is the only cribbage app that knows that.

Sweet, good-natured, casual cribbage game. The aesthetic is charming and the grandpas have real character. It lets me reminisce about playing games with my own, which is lovely because I didn't get enough time with him before he died. It's a little buggy, but I'm happy to overlook that. The game is more about the relaxing, meditative experience than intense cribbage play.
Very well done.
please update app again so it can keep working with my phone

So fun and relaxing! I love a sweet, good-natured game and this one hits the spot. Nice clean graphics and the grandpa designer is really adorable! Plus, it's awesome to keep my cribbage skills limber in between real-life games. The app itself is a little buggy, but it's nothing unplayable, at least not for me.

Buggy. Randomize feature often does not work, and be careful when you close the app because even if you win a game and return to the main menu, and then quit and close, you may end up back in the middle of the previous game when you open the app up again. Both problems exist on Android and iOS. My girlfriend plays on an iPhone. When it works, it's fun.

A cute game, easy to pick up, very relaxing. Sometimes I use it to 
de-stress or when I want to fall asleep.

Love this version of cribbage, but the latest update introduced some bugs. Most notably, every time I start a new game, it regularly gives me the same first hand, I have to quit to the menu and restart a few times until I get a first hand that I haven't had for a first hand before. Hope they fix it, it's gotten to where it feels like "what's the point of playing".
The most Canadian game ever made. A true classic. Just need to add Grandmas
Pretty fun to pass the time, though I am convinced the game actually just gives you worse cards when upping the difficulty in stead of making the grandpa a better player.
Cards definitely not random.

I thought I would enjoy it...nope. I can't win ever. Not fun. It made me hate my grandpa, seriously. This game seems to be a great idea, to reunite me with a passed love one, but the conversation is repetitive and boring. I'm sorry but this is my opinion.

I really enjoy playing Cribbage, and this is an excellent app for playing the game. It just needs a few things. The most important is a way to backup / export the Grandpas. The second is a little more variety to the sayings. And last the ability to change the colors of the pegboard and pegs. I hope the programmers considers these changes,especially the first.
Hate to say it, but I think it's rigged, lol... Grandpa wins even at lowest skill level. Uninstalling.

The cards are not random, old grandpa cleans up with big hands too many times. If you like to get beat up on a regular basis this is for you. The more I play the more I hate him. That said I keep going back to play with the old fox.
I had struggled to play this in the past, especially in the pub! This, however, has me hooked and I am now fully aware of what to do! Simply brilliant!
Pretty fun. I'd like an option for automatic counting of my points.
Clean, smooth, Cribbage game with charm. For anyone that played Cribbage with their grandpa growing up, this accurately portrays the experience.

Overall the game is one of the more pleasing versions I have played on mobile. It's visually nice and isn't too fast paced. You are required to count your hand yourself unlike a lot of the games out there. Only a couple criticisms, first I'd like to see an option where grandpa remembers that I know how to play rather than him asking me every time I start a new round with him. Also the game seems a little unstable. I've not noticed any crashes while I am playing but it doesn't handle app switching too well.
Reminds me of playing cribbage with my dad and grandpa, the silly jokes; the occasional sarcastic putdown. I really enjoy playing this game
The game needs an on screen indicator to show who's crib it is in case you miss the on screen text when grandpa says it.

Lovely, ad free game that is a pleasure to play.   I hadn't played cribbage for many years so this is a nice way to get back in to it.   There are different levels of play so it is good for beginner and the more experienced.   Love the different grandpas and their characters. My only criticism is that grandpa gets far too many 10s and 5 in his show and crib, usually when a 5 is the starter card.  This gives grandpa ridiculously high scores, but maybe that is sour grapes on my part. As well as being very enjoyable to play, with pleasing graphics, the game itself helps keep the mind sharp and some a degree of maths is involved.

Loving this game. The Grandpa creator is fun, and playing crib is super great. The game is very polished and the witty banter with the Grandpas is great. Make sure you try out Grandpas of different types, a helpful Grandpa is a great place to start for those new to playing Cribbage.
An excellent, charming take on a classic game. However gameplay is prone to crashes, especially when returning to a game open in the background.
I really enjoy building "grandpa", and the game play is great. However, it keeps crashing on my Galaxy S5, I'd say about 40% of the time. I also wish I could build a "grandma".
I wish my grandpa can play a game with me.  He has alzheimer.  😦 this game brings me good vibes even if its an ai.
I didn't know how to play cribbage but one pass through the tutorial had me on my way and now I am completely addicted! Love the art and design, part of what keeps me coming back. Great job! ☺

A lot of my childhood was watching my mom and my grandparents or great aunts and uncles play crib. With this, I get a lot of fond nostalgia being able to play a couple rounds of crib with grandpa. Great stuff
